(42, 12, 15, 21, 5, 10, 16, 'covetousness', 'Connection of Wealth and Vanity', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of wealth and possessions. Luke warns against covetousness, while Ecclesiastes highlights that loving silver leads to dissatisfaction and vanity.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
